HEADWORD: Archer fish
<hw>Arch"er fish`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small
fish (<spn>Toxotes jaculator</spn>), of the East Indies; -- so called
from its ejecting drops of water from its mouth at its prey. The name is
also applied to <spn>Ch⟦ae⟧todon rostratus</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Archership</ent>⟦br⟧
